│ Here are some thoughts about why you want to perform the action.                                                                                                                         │
│ The crash occurs when ReadDataFromGlobal processes a ConstantInt and ByteOffset exceeds the integer size in bytes. The loop condition allows ByteOffset > IntBytes, leading to           │
│ APInt::extractBits with an out-of-range bit position. We will add an early return if ByteOffset >= IntBytes and tighten the loop condition to ByteOffset < IntBytes to prevent illegal   │
│ extraction. Then we submit the patch.                                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ perl -0777 -i -pe 's/(unsigned IntBytes = unsigned\(CI->getBitWidth\/8\);\s*\n\s*)(\n?)/$1    if (ByteOffset >= IntBytes) {\n      return true;\n    }\n/s; s/for \(unsigned i = 0; i != │
│ BytesLeft && ByteOffset != IntBytes; \+\+i\)/for (unsigned i = 0; i != BytesLeft && ByteOffset < IntBytes; ++i)/' llvm/lib/Analysis/ConstantFolding.cpp && submit-patch                  │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
